,267,700.\n\nThen 25354 ×6:\n\n25354 ×6:\n\n25,000 ×6=150,000\n\n354 ×6=2,124. so total is 150,000 +2,124=152,124.\n\nSo total for 25354 ×56 is:\n\n1,267,700 +152,124 = 1,419,824.\n\nSo putting it together:\n\nOriginal total is:\n\n25354 ×50,056 = 25354×50,000 + 25354×56 = 1,267,700,000 + 1,419,824 = ?\n\nLet me calculate that:\n\n1,267,700,000 + 1,419,824.\n\nLet's add:\n\n1,267,700,000\n\n+         1,419,824\n\n= 1,269,119,824. Wait let me compute properly:\n\n1,267,700,000 + 1,419,824:\n\nStarting small:\n\n1,267,700,000 + 1,000,000 =1,268,700,000\n\nThen add 419,824:\n\n1,268,700,000 +419,824 = 1,269,119,824.\n\nThus total is 1,269,119,824.\n\nWait let me verify that.\n\nWait double-check the steps:\n\nOriginal question was 25,354 multiplied by 50,056.\n\nWhich we broke into 25,354*(50,000+56)=25,354*50,000 +25,354*56\n\nWhich is:\n\n25,354×50,000= (25,354 ×50) ×1000. Wait wait, wait: 50,000 is 5×10,000.\n\nWait wait hold on, I think I might have made a confusion earlier when breaking down.\n\nWait Let me recast the original multiplication:\n\nWait 25354 ×50056 is different from the decomposition.\n\nWait wait I think initially I thought of 25354*50,056 = what was given.\n\nWait let me verify, is it my initial breakdown or maybe I approached it incorrectly.\n\nWait let me think again.\n\nWait 25354 × 50056\n\nFirst, express 50056 as 50,000 +56, yes that's correct.\n\nSo:\n\n25,354 ×50,000 +25,354 ×56.\n\nI computed: 25,354 ×50,000 =1,267,700,000\n\nAnd 25,354 ×56 was  1,419,824 as above, so total was 1,269,119,824.\n\nBut perhaps verify the calculations again.\n\nLet me recalculate:\n\nFirst term: 25354 ×50,000:\n\nMultiply 25354 ×50,000:\n\n25354 ×50,000 is 25354 × 5 ×10,000.\n\n25354 ×5 = 126,770.\n\nSo 126,770 ×10,000=1,267,700,000.\n\nThat's correct.\n\nSecond term: 25354 ×56:\n\nBreak down 56 into 50 +6,\n\n25,354 ×50:\n\n25,354 ×5 = 126,770, then ×10 →1,267,700.\n\n25,354 ×6:\n\n25,354 ×6: let's compute:\n\n25,000 ×6=150,000\n\n354 ×6=2,124\n\nSo total 150