\n225,600 + 18,000 is 243,600, then + 612 is 244,212.\n\nSo adding 243,600 + 612 would be 244,212? Wait, let me check:\n\nWait 225,600 +18,612.\n\nStarting with 225,600 + 18,000 = 243,600.\n\nThen 243,600 + 612 = 244,212. Yep.\n\nSo 564 * 433 is 564*400 +564*33 = 225,600 + 18,612 = 244,212.\n\nWait, let me verify to make sure because it's easy to make an arithmetic mistake here.\n\nAlternatively, let's do another method. Let's verify my initial computation.\n\nAlternative approach:\n\nExpress 433 as 400 +30 + 3? Maybe multiply each part stepwise.\n\nSo 564 * 433\n\n=564*(400 + 30 + 3)\n\nHmm, let's see:\n\n=564*400 +564*30 +564*3.\n\nWhich is the same as the previous breakdown.\n\n564*400=225,600\n\n564*30= 16,920\n\n564*3=1,692\n\nSumming them:225,600 +16,920=242,520 +1,692=244,212.\n\nSame result as before. So seems like 244,212 is the correct total.\n\nBut, just to make 100% sure, perhaps perform standard multiplication.\n\nLet me set up 564 * 433:\n\nFirst, 433 multiplied by 564. Let's do it the standard way.\n\nBreak 564 into 500 +60 +4.\n\nMultiply 433*500, then 433*60, then 433*4, then sum. Let's see:\n\nSo 433*500=216,500\n\n433*60: 433*6=2598, then times 10 is 25,980\n\n433*4=1,732\n\nNow adding together:\n\n216,500 +25,980=242,480;  +1,732=242,480 +1,732=244,212\n\nSo same result.\n\nSo whether I break it as earlier or this method it's 244,212.\n\nWait just to make sure let me do 564*433.\n\nLet me verify by another way? Let's compute 564*400=225,600; 564*33.\n\nWait, 564 multiplied by 30 is 16,920; 564*3=1,692. So 16,920 +1,692 is indeed18,612.\n\n225,600+18,612=244,212.\n\nSeems consistent.\n\nAlright so I feel confident the product is 244,212.\n\nThus, I think the result is 244,212.\n\n**Final Answer**\nThe product of 564 multiplied by 433 is \\boxed{244212}.\n</think>\n\nTo find the product of 564 and 433, break it down:\n\nMultiply 564 by each part of 433 as 400 + 30 + 3:\n\n\\[\n564 \\times 400 = 225,600\n\\]\n\\[\n564 \\times 30 = 16,920\n\\]\n\\[\n564 \\times 3 = 1,692\n\\]\n\nAdding those results together:\n\n\\[\n225,600 + 16,920 = 242,520\n\\]\n\\[\n242,520 + 1,692 = 244,212\n\\]\n\nThus, multiplying 564 by 433 is 244,"], label: None, reward: {'reward': 1.0, 'accuracy': 1, 'format_score': 1}
