o 63*88 is 5544.\n\nWait let me verify using another method to make sure I didn\'t make any mistakes.\n\nAlternatively, maybe I can do multiplication the standard way:\n\n63\nx88\n——\n\nCompute 63*88. Let me try it as 63*(90 -2). Wait, because 88 is 90 minus 2, perhaps breaking it down.\n\nSo 63 times 90 minus 63*2.\n\n63*90 is 5670.\n\n63*2 is126.\n\nSo 5670 -126 =5544.\n\nSame result as before. Good. So seems like 5544 is consistent.\n\nAlternatively maybe do direct multiplication step:\n\nBut perhaps I should verify both results again.\n\nLet me compute 63*88 another way. 88 is close to 90, so breaking:\n\n(Which if using the " redistributing " idea)\n\nBut let\'s just carry the standard way properly.\n\nCompute:\n\n    63\n  x88\n  ----\n\nFirst, multiply 63 by 8: that\'s 504.\n\nThen, multiply 63 by 80 (since it\'s the tens place of 88), which is 5040.\n\nThen sum  504 +5040 = 5544.\n\nYes same result again.\n\nSo regardless of the method I use, I get 5544 as the product.\n\nTherefore, 63 times 88 is 5544.\n\nJust to double-check arithmetic:\n\nLet me test multiply 63*80 gives 5040.  63*8=504; total multiplication is 5040 + 504 = 5544.\n\nYup, seems calculated correctly both via breaking into 80 and 8, and via alternative methods.\n\nI suppose either way arrives at 5544.\n\nI can also confirm with another method. Let me perhaps use the standard multiplication:\n\nCompute 88 * 60 = 5280, then 88 * 3 =264, then 5280 + 264 * is it. Wait no... Wait no, better compute 63*80=5040 and 63*8=504 and then sum. As above.\n\nAlternatively, maybe use the number 63 *88 as multiplying 60 and 88 and 3* and so on:\n\n(60 +3)(80 +8)= Wait no, maybe better not.\n\nAlternatively, 63 times 88 is 63*(90-2)= as done earlier 5670 - 126 is 5544, confirmed as such.\n\nSeems consistent through multiple methods. So I think confidence level is sufficient, probably 5544 is the correct product.\n\n**Final Answer**\nThe product of 63 multiplied by 88 is \\boxed{5544}\n</think>\n\nTo find the result of multiplying 63 by 88, we can break down the multiplication into smaller steps for easier computation. Here is the step-by-step process:\n\n1. Break down 88 into 80 + 8.\n2. First, compute 63 × 80:\n   - 63 × 80 = 5040.\n3. Next, compute 63 × 8:\n   - 63 × 8 = 504.\n4. Add the results together:\n   - 5040 + 504 = 5544.\n\nThus, the product of 63 multiplied by 88 is \\(\\boxed{5544}\\).\n\n**Detailed Check:**\n\nUsing an alternative method:\n- Express 88 as (90 - 2):\n  - \\(63 \\times 90 = 5670\\)\n  - \\(63 \\times 2 = 126\\)\n  - Calculate \\(5670 - 126 = 5544\\)\n\nBoth methods confirm the result is 5544.\n\n\\[\n\\boxed{5544}\n\\]<｜end▁of▁sentence｜>'], label: None, reward: {'reward': 1.0, 'accuracy': 1, 'format_score': 1}
