e that sequence separated by spaces.\n\nSo the way to write it is "5 10 12 21 21"\n\nSo the string "5 10 12 21 21".\n\nLet me verify each number:\n\nOriginal list is 10, 21, 21,5,12.\n\nArrange them in order.\n\nI think sorted would indeed be the numbers in non-decreasing order.\n\nAlright, double-check:\n\nWe have four data points:\n\nThe numbers need sorting.\n\nList: [10,21,21,5,12].\n\nLet me sort numerically:\n\nFirst arrange all and sort:\n\nLooking at each number:\n\n5, 10, 12, 21,21.\n\nYes, 5 is less than 10, 10<12, then 21s follow.\n\nTherefore five sorted numbers are indeed:5,10,12,21,21.\n\nSo the required output is "5 10 12 21 21".\n\nJust make sure I didn\'t miscount or misposition any numbers.\n\nYes, counting the initial list: 10 (value10),21(21),21(21),5(5),12(12).\n\nWhen sorted:\n\n5 comes first, then10 comes, followed by 12, then next 21, then 21.\n\nHence final sorted list is indeed as I thought.\n\nAlright, now I just need to write them in the correct order inside the required format.\n\nSo the answer should be: 5 10 12 21 21.\n\nJust to confirm, perhaps writing smallest to largest as it moves sequentially.\n\nYep, no repetition in the original position but sorted correctly.\n</think>\n\nThe sorted list is \\(5, 10, 12, 21, 21\\), so the final answer is:\n\n```\n5 10 12 21 21\n```\n\nLet me now write the sorted list correctly.\n\n**Final Answer:**\n\n\\boxed{5 10 12 21 21}\n\nWait no—the requested is a single line separated by spaces, the sorted numbers are like "5 10 12 21 21".\n\nWait correct formatting: it should be written as "5 10 12 21 21"\n\nWait no wait the order should be ascending order, let me make the final line:\n\nThe sorted list is numbers arranged from smallest to largest: 5, 10, 12, 21, 21.\n\nTherefore the sorted numbers in order should be 5, 10, 12, 21, 21.\n\nHence the final required string is:\n\n"5 10 12 21 21"\n\nSo put them into a sentence with space and comma separation within a single line.\n\n**Final Answer:**\n\\boxe