ay, so term one: 52,283,000.\n\nSecond term: 7469 multiplied by 300.\n\n7469 x 300 = (7469 x 3) x 100\n\nCalculate 7469 x3:\n\n7000*3=21,000; 400*3=1200; 60*3=180; 9*3=27\n\nWait: Alternatively, 7000 + 469.\n\nWait 7469 x3: 7000*3=21000; 400*3=1200; 60*3=180; 9*3=27. So 21000 + 1200=22200; +180=22380; +27=22407\n\nThus 7469 x 3 =22,407. Then times 100 is2,240,700.\n\nSo second term is 2,240,700.\n\nThird term:7469 multiplied by 10.\n\n7469 x10=74,690.\n\nFourth term:7469 multiplied by7.\n\nWhich is again, 52,283, right? Wait compute 7469 x7 as above is 52,283.\n\nSo the four terms:\n\n1. 52,283,000\n\n2. 2,240,700\n\n3.74,690\n\n4.52,283\n\nNow let's add them all together.\n\nSo sum them term by term:\n\nFirst add 52,283,000 and 2,240,700: \n\n52,283,000 +2,240,700=54,523,700\n\nThen add 74,690:\n\n54,523,700 +74,690 = 54,598,390\n\nThen add the last term 52,283:\n\n54,598,390 +52,283=54,650,673.\n\nWait let me verify this step by step.\n\nLet me use an organized approach:\n\nCompute term1:7469 x7000=52,283,000\n\nterm2:7469x300=2,240,700\n\nterm3:7469x10=74,690\n\nterm4:7469x7=52,283\n\nNow, adding them all:\n\nStart by adding term1 and term2:\n\n52,283,000 +2,240,700: 52,283,000 + 2,240,700 = let's compute:\n\n52,283,000 + 2,240,700:\n\n52,283,000 +2,000,000 =54,283,000\n\nThen +240,700 =  54,283,000 +240,700 =54,523,700.\n\nSo sum is 54,523,700.\n\nThen add term3:74,690.\n\n54,523,700 +74,690= ?\n\n54,523,700 +70,000=54,593,700\n\n54,593,700 +4,690=54,598,390\n\nThen add term4:52,283.\n\n54,598,390 +52,283=54,650,673\n\nWait let me verify:\n\n54,598,390 +52,283:\n\nFirst add 54,598,390 +50,000 =54,648,390\n\nThen add 2,283: 54,648,390 +2,283=54,650,673.\n\nOkay, so total product is 54,650,673.\n\nBut let me double-check. Since sometimes calculation errors happen in mind.\n\nAlternatively, perhaps verify using alternate method:\n\nCompute 7469 x7317 via another way.\n\nAlternatively break into (7000 + 469)(7000 + 300 + ... no, maybe better do standard multiplicati